const e="Career Switching to Tech: Stories from Our Alumni",t="Real stories from people who made the leap from different careers into tech. Their challenges, victories, and advice for anyone considering the switch.",a="2025-01-05",r="5 min read",o="Success Stories",s="SBA Team",n="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1552664730-d307ca884978?w=800&h=450&fit=crop",i=[{type:"paragraph",text:"Switching careers is never easy, but transitioning into tech through a bootcamp has become a proven path for thousands. Here are real stories from our alumni who made the jump."},{type:"heading",text:"Sarah: From Teaching to Frontend Development"},{type:"paragraph",text:`Sarah spent 8 years as a high school math teacher before joining our bootcamp. "I loved teaching, but I wanted to create educational tools, not just use them," she explains. The transition wasn't easy—balancing bootcamp with her teaching job required sacrifice.`},{type:"quote",text:"The problem-solving skills from teaching transferred perfectly to coding. Breaking down complex concepts for students prepared me for breaking down complex code."},{type:"paragraph",text:`Today, Sarah works as a frontend developer at an edtech startup, building the tools she once wished she had in her classroom. Her advice? "Don't underestimate the skills you already have. Career changers bring unique perspectives that fresh grads don't."`},{type:"heading",text:"Marcus: From Restaurant Management to Full-Stack Developer"},{type:"paragraph",text:'After 10 years managing restaurants, Marcus was burnt out. "I was working 70-hour weeks with no work-life balance. I knew I needed a change, but starting over at 35 felt scary."'},{type:"paragraph",text:'What surprised Marcus most was how his management experience translated to tech. "Project management, handling pressure, working with diverse teams—I used all of that in my first dev job. Plus, I was used to learning on the fly in restaurants. That mindset is crucial in tech."'},{type:"heading",text:"Common Themes Among Career Switchers"},{type:"list",items:["Most struggle with imposter syndrome initially","Transferable skills matter more than you think","Age is rarely the barrier people fear it is","Financial planning for the transition period is crucial","Support systems make or break the journey"]},{type:"heading",text:"Is It Worth It?"},{type:"paragraph",text:"We won't sugarcoat it: switching careers requires sacrifice. You'll invest time, money, and emotional energy. There will be moments of doubt. But looking at our alumni outcomes, the numbers speak for themselves."},{type:"paragraph",text:"85% of our career-switching graduates land tech jobs within 6 months. Average salary increases range from 40-80%. But beyond the numbers, there's something else: fulfillment. When we survey alumni a year after graduation, over 90% say they'd make the same decision again."},{type:"heading",text:"Advice from Those Who've Done It"},{type:"list",items:["Save at least 3-6 months of expenses before starting","Tell your support system what you need from them","Don't quit your job until you have a solid plan","Use your existing network—you'd be surprised who knows someone in tech","Remember why you started when things get tough"]},{type:"paragraph",text:"Career switching isn't for everyone, and that's okay. But if you're reading this and feeling that pull toward tech, know that it's possible. The path is challenging, but it's well-traveled. You won't be the first person to make this transition, and you certainly won't be the last."}],h={title:e,excerpt:t,date:a,readTime:r,category:o,author:s,image:n,content:i};export{s as author,o as category,i as content,a as date,h as default,t as excerpt,n as image,r as readTime,e as title};
